<Date>1573660747429<//Date><Rating>3</Rating><Review>I dont know wether to like or hate this place.   Their mechanics are great.  Buy from them was nice. As they tend to be honest about what youre getting.

But getting service from them is a nightmare.  They will use the customer's lack of expertise against them to promote their high fees or services.  They constantly use the owners manuel text to push their agenda.  So you literally have to be an expert of your own bike when conversing with them about work.

I went there for an oil change too early.  But according to the owners manuals it should be an inspection.   Instead of informing me of the potential mistake, they just agree to an oil change, have me sign an estimate with little detail.  (Mind you I made the mistake of seeing the wrong price.  I thought I saw $36.80 but it was $368.00.  My mistake)
But they not onmy did an oil change they performed an inspection without clarifying that the oil change would involve that.

They charged me 2 hours of work, even though I was literally there 2.5 hours with 30 minute buffers on each side making it about 1.5 hours of work.

Does anybody go to place for an oil change and get charged $40 for the oil change AND charge extra money for the time it took?  Usually the price of the oil change includes the time itll take for work.

Lastly these guys are certified Can-Am dealer.  But they constantly have excuses for their slow work time because "Can-Ams are complex" or "this bike is new on the market".   So I pay triple the price because their techs are in experienced?  They blamed the slow oil change on the design of my bike and it's newness on the market.   Then make me pay for it.

My advice.  Buy your bike here. Theyll do great.

But take your bike to Nor-Cal Powersports in Santa Rosa for service.   Even though their techs are slightly less experienced, they are literally half the price and they will immediately inform you of every little detail of what is going on with your bike as they work on it, including changes in price due to time or complications. 5+ stars for Speed sports.  These guys are awesome.  The entire experience(sales with Desmond, Quincy and Kregg (owner), paperwork with Nancy, Ducati technicians Mike, Don and Jack).  They excel at everything.  I will never buy another bike from any other dealer.  They treat you like family.  Kregg and Quincy kept the shop open one night when I was rear ended.  They didnt care about the bike,  they were more concerned how I was.  Kregg, Quincy and Dez are all riders.  They are extremely knowledgeable on riding and can help pick the right bike for you.  No high pressure sales or games.  Nancy,  she can work magic with anything you need, Finance, warranties etc.   The technicians,  hard to find but they treat the bike like its their own. I ride rain or shine every day to work.  I logged 13,000 miles on my Ducati Hyperstrada in 1 year,  Just upgraded to a Multistrada.  I rarely ride my Harley now as the Ducati has saved my in many situations (great techology)
Do yourself a favor,  stop by and say hi if your in the market for a Ducati, MV augusta, Polaris or Can Am.   You wont regret it.  Best price, service and shop around.< /Review>

<rate>4< /rate><Text>It's my first flight with Norwegian airlines and l was very pleased!  We booked a round trip to Paris, France with premium amenities.  We liked the oversized seats and it's functionalities. Collapsible dinner tray and tv screens.  The bathroom was clean and always replenished by the attendants. Windows tint electronically, no shades are required. A special lighting throughout the aircraft is designed to help sleeping and waking patterns. The cabin is low pressurized which helps recovering from jet lag.
It is a great new way to travel for a low fare with very scarce amenities or pay a higher fare but enjoy a first class seat and some extra perks ( free access to the 1st class lounge in all airports, priority boarding, food, beverage, blankets, earphones, no fees on luggage etc.)
Our premium fare costs us what we normally would pay for an economy coach with no frill.
Norwegian airlines with premium upgrades is the way to go!
I would have given it a 5 star but it has fee minor glitches as if now.  Counter agents were nonchalant and didn't smile at all.  They sent us to the coach waiting line when we showed them our premium status tickets.  On board, l asked for a cranberry martini, (it was on the drink menu and free for us). Hostess said she only had pineapple, coke and OJ. I replied l was ok with pineapple, then she said now wasn't a good time (!).  An hour later l pointed out another drink from their menu, she again declined to serve it.  I am thinking that their cocktail menu is just for show and they really don't offer it (deceiving).  They have readily available: beer, wine, Bailey's. Do not expect glass, silverware. All is served in disposable items.  This is what separates a true first class.     When flying with Norwegian, do not expect to be attended to with great attention, fed amazing food and more.  Instead expect to fly with a lot more room than in coach, check in quicker and receive all listed amenities. It's definitely worth flying with them.  Good value!<//Text>< pics>

<Date>1536064619524< /Date><Rating>1< /Rating><Text>Norwegian is the absolute worst. There is a reason there is an entire Facebook community dedicated to "Norwegian experiences from Hell". Every single flight with them has had issues, especially with customer service but this last experience takes the cake.

Flight from Newark to Rome scheduled to leave at 11:30, first we were delayed getting on the plane by an hour. We get on the plane and get situated (with a baby who is dead tired) and 2 HOURS after sitting on the plane we are told over the intercom that a vehicle crashed into the luggage door and they were trying to fix it but they won't be able to so our flight is being cancelled. We then sit on the plane for another hour while they "make accommodations" for everyone since it is 3am. Well when we get off the plane and get to baggage claim there is no customer service representatives and they just tell everyone to "go home" well 90% of us could not go home so we asked the flight attendants and they said our best option was to get a hotel and they would call us to rebook our flight for the next day. So we paid OUT OF POCKET for a hotel, transportation, etc.

The next day we did not receive a call so we called and spent over 3 hours on hold (this is on the "phone line dedicated to our cancellation") just to be told that they didn't have any direct flights like the one we paid extra money to book originally until 3 days later and that they didn't have "clearance" to get us on a direct flight that day so our only option was to take a flight leaving at midnight that night with a 4 hr layover in Spain.

We accepted the flight since it was our only option but of course it was a huge inconvenience as we had to pay for another day at the hotel and Babies naps were all messed up from the insanity so the flight was pretty terrible but to make it worse they kept the overhead lights in the plane on for pretty much the entire 9 hr flight so my daughter struggled to sleep. When I asked when they would turn the lights off they said when people were done eating (this was 1am NY time). Funny because I thought that was the whole reason they have individual lights on seats- so that the entire flight doesn't have to suffer.

Here is the worst part though: we file our claim so we can get reimbursed and even on their website it says that if a flight is delayed more than 6 hours you are entitled to 600 euro per reservation. Well more than a month after the issue they get back to us basically saying that because it was caused by "circumstances which could not have been avoided" they won't be compensating us.

How is an employee crashing into the luggage door not something that is preventable? How about pay more attention or don't go to work drunk? I cannot believe that Norwegian would not take responsibility for such a complete disaster. I will never be flying with them again and I would not recommend them to anyone.

Oh and here is a bonus: on our flight home Rome to Newark I was denied a cup of water for the entire 9 hr flight and my "attendant" light was ignored the entire flight even though other people around us were given water when they asked and I am a nursing mother with a baby. We were flying from London Gatwick to Los Angeles and when I tried to check-in at the kiosk, it would not read my passport. Whatever, no big deal I‚Äôll just check in at the counter. We encountered a young woman who was asking us the regular security questions about our bags being unattended, etc.. She asked if I had any sharp objects in my bag, I responded with ‚Äúyes‚Äù because I had some old WW2 bullets that were recovered from Omaha Beach from Normandy. Now I‚Äôm a history teacher back home, so it was a very important and meaningful artifact to me. They had been drained of any gunpowder, linked together so as to prevent them from ever being loaded into a gun, overall completely safe. We had ZERO trouble with previous Airlines, transporting these across Europe, but these agents immediately got VERY snippy and smart with me. They kept asking me where they were from (I had told them three times), what was my purpose in having them, and then another agent started asking me about my profession and why these would be important to me, then denied me countless times. I had to drop them at a mail off kiosk.

Already extremely annoyed, we went trough the process of weighing our bags at the counter. My husband and I had three small bags between the two of us and unknown to me, each person is only allowed 10kg to carry on. My bag was 7, his was 13. So we started stuffing clothes into my bag and slowly got to the allowed weight. By their graciousness and mercy (üôÑ), they were approved. So we weighed our check in bags, each having to be only 20kg (honestly though?? What is with Europe and these TEENY bag allowances, I miss America). We were both over by a combined weight of 5 kg which we were forced to pay 45¬£ for!! FORTY FIVE POUNDS FOR 5 KG!!! What a complete JOKE!! I get that they‚Äôre cheaper, but what made it even worse was the attendant who was just berating us with insanely pricey offers of checking a third bag and paying 9¬£ for each kg. Just awful.

I will never fly this airline again, I hardly think I‚Äôm ever flying back to Europe again. Would have rather paid more for a better airline to get the service I expect than to be treated like that ever again.

**EDIT**

I will say that the flight itself was wonderful. The crew was accommodating, kind, and very helpful. The flight was enjoyable and the aircraft was very clean and modern. <username>Sergio Stone</username><time>1533251962807</time><rating>3< /rating>< Text>
I have flown Norwegian to Europe twice  in the past year. It is less expensive than other airlines and the on-line booking and alerts are excellent.  But I may not do it again. The planes are new Boeing 787 Dreamliners, but with 9 seats per row, little front space and almost no recliner, a 10 hours flight is eternal. The video entertainment  is ok. We bought the "tasty" food package. It is not better than the non-tasty food of other airlines. The crew is indifferent, look tired or anoyed, and service did not make them happier. Pouring coffee without looking is always alarming; luckily the coffee was cold. The gates locations are at the end of the airport, with a long ride to the plane in a packed, hot bus, where we were treated by the crew like catle, complete with shouting and pressing those of us inside to accommodate more passengers, what was obviously difficult. So all the positive aspects were overshadowed by the shortcomings. I must admit that the competition with other larger, better known airlines is healthy, but they should not try to imitate them.<//Text>

<Review>Finally taking the time to write a review of our trip that we took to Europe last year 09/05/15 via Norwegian air . After some of the complaints we read about on Norwegian Air we were a little worried after we booked. But once we flew them we were beyond pleasantly surprised!

Keep in mind we also drove from Reno to Oakland and we still loved our experience with Norwegian Air.

We flew out 09/05/15 from Oakland, CA (USA) to Oslo, Norway cheaper than I could fly from Reno, NV to Las Vegas, NV.

Check in was quick and efficient as well as polite and respectful. We purchased one way cheap economy tickets

The plane was large, new, clean and crowded. But that what you get when traveling on a budget.

We booked early so my 6"4' husband had leg room near an emergency exit. I and my children are shorter than my husband and my daughter who is 5"7' felt she had enough leg room.

Each seat had a TV screen with games etc. in the seat ahead of them. These entertainment consoles are free to use unless you need to purchase headphones. My family brought headphones and we all played games, listened to music, watched downloaded TV programs or movies. This was all offered for free. I greatly appreciate this because in the old days there were one maybe 2 movies on an overseas flight and you didn't get to choose what you wanted it was chosen for you.

The console also let you see in real time where the airplane was in location to your destination. I thought this was pretty cool so did my son.

Each seat has a USB port and you can charge your phone or other device.

We paid extra for the meals and luggage. It was so worth the extra money.  I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of food, the taste the appeal. I had curry chicken and rice with veggies I can't remember what the desert was but it was tasty. Then we were served a sandwich.

The airline attendants were super friendly and sweet. All we had was carry on. We did not experience any issues or difficulties with our trip. As a matter of fact we flew three more times within Europe on this one trip via other Airlines and my whole family agrees we would fly Norwegian Air again anytime. I traveled with my husband, 18 year old daughter and 13 year old son.

Thanks Norwegian Air for making it possible for a family to afford to travel to Europe again!!< /Review>< name>
LaRena Fry</name>

< Review>
I like this airline and find it a good value for the price.  I really enjoy flying the dreamliner aircraft and the comfort of their premium economy.  Wide seats with extra legroom and personal tvs make the longer routes much more tolerable although I wish they had more choices of shows/movies.  Unfortunately, like all airlines, they could do a better job of keeping you up to date on delays.  How about periodic SMS messaging or something by the people in control instead of dumping it on the desk agents?  In general I find the desk agents very friendly and helpful.  The inflight attendants just courteous but not particularly friendly.<//Review>

(Translated by Google) Review of Norwegian Airlines.

Since I like to write reviews about absolutely everything: what I buy, what services I use, about restaurants and cafes, about airlines and so on, and today I am a level 7 guide to Google. This means 700 thousand views of my photos on reviews and 150 thousand views of my recommendations - today I want to share my review about Norwegian Airlines. Take note of who you need‚úÖ

‚úàÔ∏è The flight from London to Los Angeles took just over 11 hours. Flew a business.

Some points that I would like to note:

üëúüß≥ With a business, you can take 15 kg of hand luggage in total (bag + carry-on suitcase).
üíºüíº You can hand over 2 suitcases of 20 kg each and subsequent ones for a fee.
üçù The lounge area (business lounge) was far from the gate. Not very comfortable. There you can eat breakfast and drink. Included in the ticket price.
üí∫Very comfortable seats.
ü¶µ A lot of space in general and especially legroom. More than some other business airlines that I flew before.
üí∂ Relatively not expensive tickets.
üç≤ Delicious food. Cod with potatoes in a white sauce. Salad with goat cheese and a very, very tasty dessert. It was a dinner. For breakfast, turkey and beetroot salad and pickled beef were served.
ü•ó Whoever wanted to eat during the break could buy a tasty snack: salad, sandwich, rice noodles, or a fruit plate for a small fee.
üç∑‚òïÔ∏è Drinks at any time and in any quantity including wine (white or red), beer, juices, tea, coffee. Only the most refined and unique alcoholic drinks were available for a fee.

In general, I really liked it. I recommend üëç

He was good at making the Smart Switch from my S9 to my new S20 FE, as well as the SIM & SD transfers, a cinch. I'm also grateful that the associates didn't mind allowing me as much time as I needed to stay inside the shop and get acquainted with my new phone before I left the shop. I also appreciate that he was attentive of my experience with the new phone initialization experience. And I'm glad I asked to pick the number for the new line for the BOGO offer. I chose a # that seems easy to remember.
Also, good job, this T-Mobile location, for still having a couple S20 FE's in stock! After realizing the fiasco of S21's lack of an SD slot, more S20 series should've been kept at T-Mobile locations, just in case! Could make several customers very happy. I had called ~9 other closest T-Mobile stores beforehand, seeking the S20 FE, and none had it in stock. Placing the S20 FE on order would've taken 5 weeks! Thankfully my diligent search led me to this T-Mobile location that still had a couple left!

Room for improvement (Peter):
- I had some questions that Peter couldn't or didn't directly answer. For example, he and his co-worker did not know whether the S20 FE heating issue from 2020 has been resolved. (FYI I've been using it for a day and have not detected any heating issue.) I also asked why Smart Switch needed Wi-Fi access when it's just data transfer between two local phones. He said something about how it requires Internet, Bluetooth... which didn't clearly answer my question; it's still between two phones two inches from each other. But afterward, I realized that Internet is needed cuz the new phone needs to download the same apps that the old phone has.
- He could've been a little friendlier (service with a smile, warm and welcoming tone and demeanor, etc.) but I wasn't too sensitive about that.
- I noticed he spoke Viet rly fast to the elderly Viet couple. He had to repeat himself twice cuz the elderly man couldn't catch Peter's fast speech. I would've spoken slower from the beginning. Empathy. Perhaps he was just tired cuz it was late in the day.
- It seemed like if I didn't ask to pick the number myself, Peter would've chosen a random one. If so, I'd likely have gotten a random, hard-to-remember #. So if you the customer gets the chance, remember to ask to pick your own hopefully easy-to-remember #!

As for the slightly awkward store location:
Entering and exiting the P lot is sketchy. I almost got run over entering the P lot through the narrow back alley when some reckless ABG driver popped up  and barely managed to swerve around me. Later, I almost got hit again when another ABG backed outta her spot without checking whether the road is clear. So be mindful of your road neighbors!

<rating>1<//rating>< Text>
I only use Costco for my dogs medication and unfortunately have been using them for years. The only reason I have kept with them is because my veterinarian always said they had the best price and my dog is epileptic and needs this medication to keep her well.

But I have had to beat my head against the wall with them every single month with them not getting the fax from the veterinarian for her refills!!  My veterinarian sends the fax in no less than 3 times each month!  The lady at the front desk is really the sweetheart and I hate going in there upset every time. I asked if there is a problem with filling a pet's medication. I've asked if there is anything I can do to help make the process easier and I'm just at a loss.

I have finally given up and am taking my pet's medication to be filled at another pharmacy, it will cost me quite a bit more...like almost $75 MORE EACH MONTH  but at this point I'm finding it worth it to save the headache.</Text>

Down side is they are always busy and your 1 hour trip can be 2 in a blink of an eye. But all the Kirkland Products are super high quality in my opinion and you literally can't beat the demos!!!
Super friendly staff and their Bakery is the best!<//Text>

<rating>5<//rating>< text>
Costco has a terrific price on real hearing h. People that belong to Kaiser think they're getting a deal at the Kaiser price of $6,000. The Costco price for the same instruments is only $1,600 and the only difference is the Costco units do not use rechargeable batteries. But for me, that's okay because I found rechargeables on my previous pair to be a bit of a nuisance. They had to be inserted into the charger every night. With replacement batteries they're good for a week and they're totally portable and I'm not tied to having to charge them every night. You're much more convenient that way during travel.< /text>

Consistently bad experience at the food court with weekend wait times. I don't see any point to the pick-up line as it always moves slower causing customer frustration. Also if you want to cancel you have to wander over to the last checkstand and hope someone is there to issue a refund. <Pictures>None</Pictures><user>116015078101689058205< /user><Review>We really like Costco.  And, we have figured out how to buy and use products in volume.  Of course, there are certain things that we must go to a local grocery store, or other type of store, to buy in smaller quantities, since we just can't use so much of that product before it goes bad.

We are fortunate here in Livermore because this local Costco is a Corporate Store.  This means they use this store to test items before they are distributed to other Costco's.  In the past, we have really found some good deals on items they decided not to carry and then significantly reduced the prices to clear them from the store.

We also enjoy getting a bite to eat at their "Food Court".   Good prices for the quantity and quality.

Costco is well worth the yearly membership fee.< /Review><Name>Greg Knowles<//Name>< date>

<Time>1490389742584<//Time><Rate>1<//Rate>< Review>
Never met such rude costco employees in my life. Like others have said in the reviews your better off going to the tracey or danville costco for multiple reasons. I prefer to make it an event and drive to the concord costco. They always have what i need. Never run out of sour cream or other necessities and they have the best wine stewart out of any costco i have been to. Concords wine stewarts name is Randy and he gets awesome wine brought into the Concord store. You would think Concord is the corporate store because they truly set the high standards you expect and the employees treat you with respect. I rate san leandro costo, san francisco costco, richmond costco, fremontcostco, and danville costco way above livermores as well. The only two costcos i have been to and been so disappointed in are livermore costco and redwood city costco ( the other rude costco which never has the right prices on items) and you can never get assistance without attitude from the employees.< /Review>

<Text>I shop here every week, but only cause the location is so close and convenient.

Complaints:
1. This Costco's stock is never consistent. Even everyday items like sour cream, or yogurt go suddenly missing for months on end. I have to go to the Tracy location every once in a while when this location stops carrying some items.

2. This Costco is the master of moving around merchandise. A few weeks ago after failing to find granola bars, even a Costco employee couldn't find them despite having over 1,000 boxes in inventory. Prepare yourself for a constant scavenger hunt.

3. This location is ALWAYS BUSY. Like, ridiculously busy. Like, driving around looking for ANY parking spot for 30 minutes on a Saturday busy. If I'm not in the mood to fight the crowd, I'll go to the Tracy location which is always much more mild.

4. The water temperature of the bathroom sink in the men's restroom is set to "Hot Lava". My kid burned his hands it was so hot. I mentioned it to several Costco employees (over several visits...it's ALWAYS scalding), no one seems to care.

Do NOT try to order items online from Costco! You will be signing up for a journey down a rabbit hole with delivery mishaps, missed appointments, and partial installations. The online system makes everything seems too easy and doable. We ordered this package in July. Once we received the notification that the appliances were delivered locally, we were given a # to call for delivery and installation. After weeks of not hearing back from them, we drove the Livermore location trying to obtain more information. At which point, we were given another # to call and resolve ‚Äòour issue.‚Äô That call did result in us getting an actual appointment which the delivery company called and rescheduled. At one point, even though  no delivery was made, an installation person showed up to install the appliances that we never received. Finally, the appliances showed up but the delivery person only installed two and left the other two sitting in big boxes in the  middle of the room. Called back twice to inquire who is going to install them but no response. Called back Costco again for clarification but no response. Meanwhile, the payment was deducted back in July. Unless, you have time to play their games, just stay away! This process is not worth a few hundred dollars you will save shopping from Coscto.</Text>

< text>
This location is conveniently located off I-580 in Livermore. The parking lot gets really congested since its small. They do have a gas station that stays busy, but it makes it easier being a one stop shop. I love all of the free samples you get on the weekends, and it's helped me find different dinner ideas. They offer everything from bulk food, optometrist services, travel services, auto services, and much more. We usually go here at least once a month to stock up on things. Diapers and wipes are reasonably priced as well as toilet paper, paper towels and other stuff you use daily.</text>
